and Stone Mountain will
generously advance you a month's

89
00:12:08,782 --> 00:12:10,366
supply of these items,

90
00:12:10,677 --> 00:12:11,977
payment to be deducted.

91
00:12:12,578 --> 00:12:15,413
I'm going to take you over
to camp now where you'll be livin'.

92
00:12:15,414 --> 00:12:19,284
There's some Italian gentleman
that are very eager to meet you.

93
00:12:19,585 --> 00:12:23,468
Rentals will be
for one room, 2.50 a month.

94
00:12:23,589 --> 00:12:26,725
Company rule, no more than
two people to one room,

95
00:12:26,726 --> 00:12:28,527
children included.

96
00:12:28,828 --> 00:12:31,363
Electricity, where that is feasible,

97
00:12:31,414 --> 00:12:32,797
will be 1 dollar a month.

98
00:12:43,442 --> 00:12:44,957
Mrs. Radnor?

99
00:12:45,188 --> 00:12:46,545
Yes.

100
00:12:47,046 --> 00:12:49,614
My name is Joe Kenehan.

101
00:12:52,084 --> 00:12:54,520
I'm going to be in town for a bit and

102
00:12:54,571 --> 00:12:56,027
your place here was recommended.

103
00:12:56,168 --> 00:12:57,256
What do you do?

104
00:13:00,026 --> 00:13:03,495
Uh, I guess I'm looking for work.

105
00:13:03,696 --> 00:13:05,130
You with the Company?

106
00:13:05,631 --> 00:13:08,667
The company?
- If you ain't with the Company,

107
00:13:08,668 --> 00:13:09,618
there ain't no work.

108
00:13:12,972 --> 00:13:17,042
Look mister, don't act the lamb with me.
What's your business here?

109
00:13:17,143 --> 00:13:18,543
- Mama!

110
00:13:18,544 --> 00:13:21,951
- Mama, it's Hillard!
Them scabs done it, up the line a mile...

111
00:13:22,011 --> 00:13:23,983
They was all coloured this time,
they bust his nose!

112
00:13:24,004 --> 00:13:25,217
You got any ice?

113
00:13:25,248 --> 00:13:26,851
- Some in the back.
Go fetch me two chunks about this big

114
00:13:26,872 --> 00:13:28,086
and a piece of rag.

115
00:13:28,087 --> 00:13:30,556
You a doctor?
- No, but I seen my share

116
00:13:30,657 --> 00:13:32,158
of broken noses.

117
00:13:33,159 --> 00:13:35,160
Now just put it up in the air, buddy,
just like your watching

118
00:13:35,161 --> 00:13:36,161
the clouds.

119
00:13:37,229 --> 00:13:39,331
We'll get that bleeding stopped.

120
00:13:39,332 --> 00:13:40,632
I ga my liggid...

121
00:13:40,633 --> 00:13:43,001
Say what?
- He said he got his licks in.

122
00:13:43,002 --> 00:13:46,237
Seems to be all the men around here
care about, wives and kids are starving,

123
00:13:46,238 --> 00:13:47,939
so long as they've got their licks in...

124
00:13:48,008 --> 00:13:50,722
It's just frustration, is all

125
00:13:50,743 --> 00:13:53,158
when you can't take care
of them you care about.

126
00:13:53,179 --> 00:13:54,216
I know, it ain't their fault.

127
00:13:54,247 --> 00:13:55,215
Here you go.

128
00:13:55,316 --> 00:13:57,250
This freezes up all them little veins inside.

129
00:13:57,281 --> 00:13:59,926
It's just so they close up and they

130
00:13:59,957 --> 00:14:01,954
don't let any more blood out.

131
00:14:02,085 --> 00:14:02,821
You a doctor?

132
00:14:03,342 --> 00:14:04,290
No.

133
00:14:05,991 --> 00:14:08,160
I'm just a guy looking for a place to stay.

134
00:14:09,361 --> 00:14:10,962
5 dollars a week cash.

135
00:14:11,863 --> 00:14:13,858
That includes dinner and clean sheets.

136
00:14:14,899 --> 00:14:16,601
Hope I'm not making a mistake.

137
00:14:17,803 --> 00:14:19,605
Name is Joe Kenehan.

138
00:14:25,978 --> 00:14:29,580
- Well, mostly I work for the railroads,
laying track.

139
00:14:29,611 --> 00:14:30,983
Kansas, Missouri...

140
00:14:31,984 --> 00:14:34,886
I went out west for a bit
and worked in a lumber camp.

141
00:14:37,123 --> 00:14:39,324
A little of whatever pays an honest dollar.

142
00:14:39,565 --> 00:14:42,918
I'm a coalminer.
At least until we come out I was.

143
00:14:42,949 --> 00:14:44,997
Had me over in section 3.
I was a trapper boy.

144
00:14:46,398 --> 00:14:49,110
Ain't you a little young?
- I'm almost 15.

145
00:14:49,301 --> 00:14:52,070
There are some in there younger than me.

146
00:14:52,471 --> 00:14:53,875
Of course with the strike now

147
00:14:53,906 --> 00:14:54,973
I work mostly on running this place.

148
00:14:55,174 --> 00:14:57,108
I help a little, don't I?

149
00:14:58,109 --> 00:14:59,911
It's gonna be a long one.

150
00:14:59,912 --> 00:15:02,547
That superintendent
at Stone Mountain he said

151
00:15:02,548 --> 00:15:06,384
he'd go broke before he let
one union sumbitch so much as step

152
00:15:06,385 --> 00:15:07,619
into his coalmine.

153
00:15:07,620 --> 00:15:09,288
- Danny...
Sorry, ma'am,

154
00:15:09,329 --> 00:15:10,723
but that's what he said.

155
00:15:11,524 --> 00:15:13,758
Daniel is a preacher.
- Is that so?

156
00:15:13,759 --> 00:15:15,927
- You ought to hear him testify.

157
00:15:16,328 --> 00:15:17,696
What church you with?

158
00:15:18,297 --> 00:15:21,066
Well, round here there's
the missionary folk... they's

159
00:15:21,067 --> 00:15:23,935
Hardshell Baptists and then
there's the free will folks which is

160
00:15:23,936 --> 00:15:25,070
your Softshell Baptists.

161
00:15:25,071 --> 00:15:26,406
Right now I preach for both.

162
00:15:28,007 --> 00:15:29,240
[ KNOCK AT DOOR ]

163
00:15:29,241 --> 00:15:30,476
I'll get it.

164
00:15:31,477 --> 00:15:34,266
Daniel is gonna preach tonight
over at the missionary.

165
00:15:36,282 --> 00:15:38,049
I never was religious myself.

166
00:15:38,750 --> 00:15:40,218
- It's Sephus, mama.

167
00:15:41,619 --> 00:15:42,787
Hello, Elma...

168
00:15:43,788 --> 00:15:45,190
Mrs. Knightes

169
00:15:45,191 --> 00:15:46,260
- Hello, Sephus.

170
00:15:47,251 --> 00:15:49,228
I come to have a word with your new boarder,

171
00:15:51,349 --> 00:15:52,365
if he don't mind.

172
00:15:55,067 --> 00:15:56,602
Excuse me.

173
00:16:12,718 --> 00:16:15,420
Claims he's the fella the union sent us.

174
00:16:17,823 --> 00:16:18,757
             Can you prove it? 

175
00:16:22,561 --> 00:16:23,995
        Don't take nothing to have
           a card printed up.

176
00:16:25,798 --> 00:16:28,066
 I guess you'll just have to trust me.

177
00:16:30,236 --> 00:16:32,171
        Who wrote "The Iron Hill"?

178
00:16:33,172 --> 00:16:35,907
          Jack London.
  - Where's Joe Hill buried at?

179
00:16:36,108 --> 00:16:39,310
    All over the world.
They scattered his ashes.

180
00:16:39,311 --> 00:16:41,746
Which eye is Big Bill Hayward missing?

181
00:16:46,152 --> 00:16:48,753
         His right one.
  - How did Frank Little die?

182
00:16:48,754 --> 00:16:52,023
Butte, Montana.
They hung him from a railroad trestle.

183
00:16:54,894 --> 00:16:57,128
     - You know your stuff.

184
00:16:57,129 --> 00:17:00,498
I was with the Wobbley's.
        - Me too,

185
00:17:00,499 --> 00:17:02,133
 back when it meant something.

186
00:17:03,602 --> 00:17:07,238
        One big union.
    - Not around here buddy.

187
00:17:08,941 --> 00:17:10,308
          C.E. Lively...

188
00:17:10,309 --> 00:17:13,511
 this is my restaurant.
Fellas are waitin'.

189
00:17:20,619 --> 00:17:22,887
 They don't give a damn
whether we live or die

190
00:17:22,888 --> 00:17:25,657
  just so long as they get
the coal out of the ground.

191
00:17:25,658 --> 00:17:29,427
They had us pulling pillars and
the roof was working, you know

192
00:17:29,428 --> 00:17:32,030
like it does before it's going to fall down.

193
00:17:32,031 --> 00:17:34,933
 If I say I ain't dying in here
         and walk away

194
00:17:34,934 --> 00:17:38,703
they'll put me down
in some damn puddle in a 2 foot seam

195
00:17:38,704 --> 00:17:42,941
  and no air to breathe...
  A man can't mine coal that way.

196
00:17:42,942 --> 00:17:45,710
They're just pushing us
further than we can go.

197
00:17:45,711 --> 00:17:48,413
 - The check wayman he'll take
50 pound off your load for slate

198
00:17:48,414 --> 00:17:49,814
when there ain't a pebble in it.

199
00:17:49,815 --> 00:17:52,751
 It's down in the bottom he'll say
 where they ain't no looking for it.

200
00:17:52,852 --> 00:17:55,787
Then they raise the prices at
the Company Store the same goddamn week

201
00:17:55,788 --> 00:17:57,655
that they lower the tonnage rate.

202
00:17:57,656 --> 00:17:59,991
And they still ain't rock dusted
        that damn hole.

203
00:17:59,992 --> 00:18:03,027
 [ PREACHER ]  Who'm I talking about?
            - Jesus

204
00:18:03,028 --> 00:18:04,362
    I can't hear you!
            - Jesus!

205
00:18:04,363 --> 00:18:07,298
    I still can't hear you!
            - Jesus!!

206
00:18:07,299 --> 00:18:10,335
  Jesus Christ our lord!
  Do you know His name?

207
00:18:10,336 --> 00:18:11,836
     Hallelujah, say yeah!

208
00:18:11,837 --> 00:18:17,775
Have you felt the warming
 comfort of His precious love?

209
00:18:17,776 --> 00:18:20,078
          Praise Jesus!

210
00:18:20,079 --> 00:18:21,613
     Praise His holy name!

211
00:18:21,614 --> 00:18:23,781
Praise His blessed spirit!

212
00:18:23,782 --> 00:18:29,354
  Praise His everlasting love!
    Jesus Christ our lord!

213
00:18:29,355 --> 00:18:32,457
Listen to me now, listen to me.

214
00:18:34,093 --> 00:18:38,229
    The prince of darkness

215
00:18:40,032 --> 00:18:42,958
    is upon the land!

216
00:18:43,469 --> 00:18:44,636
              Amen!

217
00:18:44,637 --> 00:18:50,608
Now in the bible his name is Beelzebub,

218
00:18:51,949 --> 00:18:54,579
    Lord of the flies.

219
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:58,583
Right now on earth today

220
00:18:58,944 --> 00:19:01,887
    his name is bolshevick!

221
00:19:01,988 --> 00:19:05,924
 Socialist!, communist!, union man!

222
00:19:05,925 --> 00:19:12,397
 Lord of untruth, sower of evil seed,
enemy of all that is good

223
00:19:12,398 --> 00:19:15,266
  and pure and this creature

224
00:19:18,003 --> 00:19:20,505
        walks among us.

225
00:19:23,008 --> 00:19:26,244
 What are we gonna do about it?

226
00:19:51,303 --> 00:19:54,238
 First thing we got to have is
 all of these niggers

227
00:19:54,239 --> 00:19:56,708
and all these dagos that come
in here to take our jobs

228
00:19:56,739 --> 00:19:57,810
             thrown out of the mines.

229
00:19:57,951 --> 00:20:00,715
Mines, hell! They got 'em in our houses,

230
00:20:00,746 --> 00:20:02,317
they're setting at our tables right now

231
00:20:02,348 --> 00:20:05,019
and they're sleeping in our beds
 while we're out living under a

232
00:20:05,050 --> 00:20:06,955
 piece of canvas at
          the back of the hollar.

233
00:20:07,186 --> 00:20:09,757
I been a union man my whole life.

234
00:20:09,788 --> 00:20:13,328
I know the story with these
coal operators and their gun thugs.

235
00:20:13,359 --> 00:20:16,828
 The only thing they understand
  is the bad end of a bullet.

236
00:20:17,329 --> 00:20:20,365
If we show 'em, we just as soon
 blow up their damn mines than

237
00:20:20,366 --> 00:20:23,968
 seen them worked by a bunch of scabs
and then they gonna listen.

238
00:20:24,869 --> 00:20:27,805
- Someone is coming, it's Alex.
He got someone.

239
00:20:45,991 --> 00:20:47,525
    Where did you find him?

240
00:20:47,826 --> 00:20:49,727
 He come right up on the steps.

241
00:20:49,828 --> 00:20:54,158
They told me that C.E. Lively's
is where the union mens meet.

242
00:20:54,199 --> 00:20:55,034
              So?

243
00:20:57,669 --> 00:20:59,270
    I got business with the union.

244
00:21:01,573 --> 00:21:03,208
          That so?

245
00:21:03,309 --> 00:21:04,890
     What's your name, son?

246
00:21:05,411 --> 00:21:08,346
They calls me "Few Clothes".
