01:01:30,000 --> 01:01:31,600
 Where's all the men gone to?

740
01:01:38,708 --> 01:01:40,677
That changes the whole picture.

741
01:01:41,878 --> 01:01:45,494
  What I'm saying is unions is
     fine for some things,

742
01:01:45,845 --> 01:01:48,650
 but for other things a man's
   got to go on his own.

743
01:01:50,151 --> 01:01:52,087
  Of course that's up to you.

744
01:01:53,957 --> 01:01:55,191
            Roscoe...

745
01:01:59,796 --> 01:02:04,133
You make sindacato,
you do what the sindacato say.

746
01:02:04,534 --> 01:02:07,303
        I listen to Joe.

747
01:02:09,839 --> 01:02:10,941
          Few Clothes...

748
01:02:12,942 --> 01:02:15,143
We gonna be shooting white folks, right?

749
01:02:15,944 --> 01:02:17,753
        That's the idea.

750
01:02:19,949 --> 01:02:22,551
  People hear about black folks
shooting white folks,

751
01:02:22,552 --> 01:02:26,321
no matter what it's for,
there's going to be hell to pay.

752
01:02:27,757 --> 01:02:29,360
        You gotta point.

753
01:02:31,561 --> 01:02:33,196
        Well then,

754
01:02:34,497 --> 01:02:37,065
if you gentleman will excuse us...

755
01:02:48,344 --> 01:02:53,943
You people have been put out
of Stone Mountain Mine housing

756
01:02:54,884 --> 01:03:00,022
and some of you have seen fit to
take along certain items

757
01:03:00,523 --> 01:03:03,885
of food, furniture and clothing
 that don't belong to you but

758
01:03:03,926 --> 01:03:05,360
     belong to the Company.

759
01:03:09,165 --> 01:03:11,436
As of the day of the strike

760
01:03:11,477 --> 01:03:15,704
your script ceased to be legal tender,

761
01:03:15,905 --> 01:03:18,569
meaning that any item of food,
clothing, and furniture

762
01:03:18,610 --> 01:03:21,703
not paid for in cash money

763
01:03:22,644 --> 01:03:25,347
must be turned over to me

764
01:03:25,683 --> 01:03:30,319
 and my deputies and I suggest
     that you all cooperate.

765
01:03:31,920 --> 01:03:33,889
     See, my boys,              

766
01:03:34,490 --> 01:03:38,894
they didn't get much sleep last night,
so they're kinda jumpy.

767
01:03:40,296 --> 01:03:43,892
 Besides we got the law on our side.

768
01:03:43,933 --> 01:03:47,369
- You ain't no law !
You got to slip around the real law !

769
01:03:48,040 --> 01:03:50,172
You just got guns is all.

770
01:03:50,273 --> 01:03:50,953
         You just thugs.

771
01:03:54,310 --> 01:03:56,044
  Yeah, maybe your right, sonny,

772
01:03:56,045 --> 01:03:58,951
    we just got guns.

773
01:03:59,152 --> 01:04:01,383
 You still got to hand in them goods.

774
01:04:01,684 --> 01:04:03,820
     Yellow scab-herder, you !

775
01:04:06,121 --> 01:04:07,980
Hillard, you get up from there.    

776
01:04:08,091 --> 01:04:10,359
- You gotta list of goods?

777
01:04:12,655 --> 01:04:13,864
        Don't need one.

778
01:04:14,065 --> 01:04:17,233
How you gonna know what belongs
to the company and what don't?

779
01:04:18,134 --> 01:04:19,803
      He's the red, Hickey.

780
01:04:21,604 --> 01:04:22,740
    He's the agitator.

781
01:04:27,076 --> 01:04:29,812
Everybody, you see,
I don't got a gun on me.

782
01:04:35,785 --> 01:04:40,155
 What good do you think
that's going to do you, red?

783
01:04:40,456 --> 01:04:43,659
You shoot me folks'll know it was murder.

784
01:04:43,760 --> 01:04:47,095
 Well, that's some cold comfort.

785
01:04:47,946 --> 01:04:50,332
Now you listen to me, red...

785
01:04:51,296 --> 01:04:52,632
[ GUNSHOT ]

785
01:04:56,096 --> 01:04:56,932
[ GUNSHOT ]

786
01:05:09,152 --> 01:05:10,786
         We was huntin'.

787
01:05:12,623 --> 01:05:15,224
 You folks are making
 an awful lot of commotion.

788
01:05:16,025 --> 01:05:17,393
 You scaredt all the game away.

789
01:05:19,462 --> 01:05:20,963
      This your machine?

790
01:05:22,533 --> 01:05:24,767
    Heard it last night, too.

791
01:05:25,008 --> 01:05:26,957
It's an offense to the ear.

792
01:05:27,278 --> 01:05:30,005
Hold it pops,
 you're talking to the law here.

793
01:05:31,206 --> 01:05:33,843
     He ask you anything?

794
01:05:34,444 --> 01:05:37,746
  Where did you get that thing, pal?
  Spanish war?

795
01:05:41,451 --> 01:05:43,085
             Nope,

796
01:05:43,886 --> 01:05:46,388
    war between the states.

797
01:05:46,689 --> 01:05:50,625
You all get in this machine and
get back into town where you belong.

798
01:05:51,626 --> 01:05:55,464
 Ain't but one law out here
 and that's the law of nature.

799
01:05:58,835 --> 01:06:01,254
Let's get the hell out of here.

800
01:06:24,927 --> 01:06:27,796
  Folks try and keep the
  noise down you'll do fine.

801
01:06:28,897 --> 01:06:31,367
 Help yourself to the bird
 and the rabbit.

802
01:06:32,068 --> 01:06:35,001
 You see any hogs they probably ours.

803
01:06:35,123 --> 01:06:37,172
We'd appreciate it if you'd leave them be.

804
01:06:38,641 --> 01:06:40,276
        Good day to you.

805
01:06:51,320 --> 01:06:52,671
    Are you okay, Joe?

806
01:06:52,822 --> 01:06:55,924
  Yeah, I'll be all right
  if it weren't for my ribs.

807
01:06:56,860 --> 01:06:58,360
     Who were those people?

808
01:06:58,431 --> 01:06:59,461
       - Rossums, mostly,

809
01:06:59,462 --> 01:07:01,031
      and a Shuttleworth.

810
01:07:02,832 --> 01:07:05,100
         They miners?
- You never find them folks near a hole.

811
01:07:05,101 --> 01:07:07,903
They had most of their land
stole by the company.

812
01:07:08,004 --> 01:07:10,439
    They's hill people.
  - Foothill people really,

813
01:07:10,469 --> 01:07:12,073
     your genuine hill people.

814
01:07:12,074 --> 01:07:13,575
     They can be dangerous.

815
01:07:23,586 --> 01:07:25,453
Now the thing you gotta remember, son

816
01:07:25,454 --> 01:07:28,356
 is your fuse burns 1 foot per minute.

817
01:07:28,357 --> 01:07:30,892
Make it too long, they might see it.

818
01:07:32,893 --> 01:07:34,262
      Make it too short,

819
01:07:34,263 --> 01:07:37,532
we'll all be meeting you
on the other side.

820
01:07:38,367 --> 01:07:39,434
    [ KNOCKING AT DOOR ]

821
01:07:52,448 --> 01:07:53,181
            Damn it.

822
01:08:00,923 --> 01:08:02,952
          Air shaft #4.

823
01:08:04,093 --> 01:08:06,428
      Go out the back way.

824
01:08:31,821 --> 01:08:34,322
 Where is all our
other friends tonight, Miss Elma?

825
01:08:34,523 --> 01:08:36,992
 They get tired of the chuck or what?

826
01:08:38,461 --> 01:08:40,963
 I think that old bitty went on strike,

827
01:08:41,064 --> 01:08:42,965
    laid down her teeth	and protested.

828
01:08:43,366 --> 01:08:45,984
 They're just particular about
      who they eat with.

829
01:08:46,055 --> 01:08:47,435
- What about you, Miss Elma?

830
01:08:47,936 --> 01:08:49,537
      Are you particular?

831
01:08:51,741 --> 01:08:53,899
 Stone Mountain didn't
 hold the lease here you two...

832
01:08:53,930 --> 01:08:56,478
- Stone Mountain didn't hold lease
 here you'd be peddling puntang

833
01:08:56,519 --> 01:08:59,848
 down in cinder bottom so just
shut your mouth about it.

834
01:09:10,993 --> 01:09:13,396
  Where's your little preacher tonight?

835
01:09:28,678 --> 01:09:31,145
  Bitch got no table manners.

836
01:09:45,394 --> 01:09:46,427
             Elma?

837
01:09:52,168 --> 01:09:53,969
You know where Danny is?

838
01:09:55,104 --> 01:09:58,039
 No. I don't know where anybody is.

839
01:09:58,240 --> 01:10:00,808
  Ain't nobody wants to tell me either.

840
01:10:03,879 --> 01:10:07,582
        You okay?
    - Yeah just tired is all.

841
01:10:08,985 --> 01:10:12,053
  I been working all day.
  This place...

842
01:10:14,490 --> 01:10:16,626
        I been working...

843
01:10:18,627 --> 01:10:24,332
the day they burned my husband I
started and I been working and it...

844
01:10:24,333 --> 01:10:26,369
      It don't never stop.

845
01:10:27,370 --> 01:10:30,405
        I get so tired

846
01:10:30,406 --> 01:10:32,574
              and

847
01:10:32,575 --> 01:10:35,576
    there ain't nobody.
        - Look it's hard.

848
01:10:36,462 --> 01:10:38,747
  It's hard being on your own.

849
01:10:46,822 --> 01:10:48,424
You don't know nothing about it.



849
01:10:48,452 --> 01:10:50,884
[ SOUND OF EXPLOSION ]

850
01:10:51,560 --> 01:10:54,096
- We're in business buddy,
 let's get going.

851
01:10:59,035 --> 01:11:03,439
     [ TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS ]

852
01:11:04,040 --> 01:11:06,256
         What is it?
- Sounds like dynamite

853
01:11:06,287 --> 01:11:09,612
up at the mine.
Might be that #5 shaft.

854
01:11:22,625 --> 01:11:25,126
     Might be some shootin'.

855
01:11:28,531 --> 01:11:33,568
   - Hillard! Hillard!

856
01:11:33,569 --> 01:11:36,838
- You seen my boy?
Anybody seen my boy, Hillard?

857
01:11:37,940 --> 01:11:41,210
That'll be the Baldwins.
			- Hillard!

858
01:11:49,051 --> 01:11:51,586
Anybody seen my Hillard?

859
01:11:56,025 --> 01:11:57,525
          [ GUN COCKS ]

860
01:12:15,613 --> 01:12:18,213
      [ CAR ENGINE RUNNING ]

861
01:12:35,366 --> 01:12:37,466
     - It's Baldwins up the hill!

862
01:12:38,467 --> 01:12:40,435
  Shoot low boys!
  Cut 'em down!

863
01:12:48,577 --> 01:12:51,149
 You fellas get on out of here,
      I'll hold 'em back.

864
01:12:59,756 --> 01:13:00,856
         Reese! Reese, get up!

865
01:13:06,495 --> 01:13:08,030
         Sephus, c'mon!

866
01:13:15,404 --> 01:13:17,973
- Okay boys, let's spread out,
he's here somewhere.

867
01:13:18,274 --> 01:13:21,042
- I got him. He's over here.
      [ C.E. ] Hold it boys, it's me.  

868
01:13:21,543 --> 01:13:24,045
 Hold your fire boys, it's C.E.

869
01:13:25,346 --> 01:13:26,715
       - You all right?

870
01:13:27,816 --> 01:13:30,018
  - You'd better get back to camp.

871
01:13:36,492 --> 01:13:38,261
             Judias.

872
01:13:39,662 --> 01:13:41,263
        - Hold his leg.

873
01:13:42,264 --> 01:13:44,365
      Hold it, hold, hold.

874
01:13:45,634 --> 01:13:48,937
Now I'm just going to pull this
    back from your leg, boy.

875
01:13:50,172 --> 01:13:52,174
 Gimme back that knife, Hillard.

876
01:13:52,975 --> 01:13:54,610
 - Hey, what happened?             

877
01:13:55,311 --> 01:13:58,706
We was sold.
Them Baldwins come up from behind.

878
01:13:58,747 --> 01:14:00,852
 Known right where we was laying out.

879
01:14:00,883 --> 01:14:03,452
- They know'd when the men
was out of camp today, too.

880
01:14:04,353 --> 01:14:06,158
    How's she feelin', buddy?

881
01:14:06,789 --> 01:14:09,858
 You made it.
 I thought we lost you back there.

882
01:14:09,929 --> 01:14:11,492
Well, I got off a couple of rounds...

883
01:14:11,493 --> 01:14:12,927
  buried myself in the leaves.

884
01:14:13,728 --> 01:14:15,564
Seen Reese Hadley go down, though.

885
01:14:15,605 --> 01:14:17,332
    Sephus get back?

886
01:14:17,833 --> 01:14:19,568
    I don't think so.

887
01:14:20,169 --> 01:14:22,203
 You see what happens
 when you pick up a gun!

888
01:14:22,204 --> 01:14:26,808
 All I see is them niggers and
dagos weren't there tonight and

889
01:14:26,809 --> 01:14:29,310
 we was sold and somebody gonna pay.

890
01:14:35,484 --> 01:14:37,655
 Something bad is happening out there.

891
01:14:37,686 --> 01:14:38,988
        Those guns.

892
01:14:39,289 --> 01:14:40,782
Hunting party, that's all.

893
01:14:40,823 --> 01:14:42,751
    Now, where was I?

894
01:14:43,092 --> 01:14:46,127
    "time to put all shyness"...

895
01:14:46,128 --> 01:14:49,330
 Time to put all shyness aside

896
01:14:52,001 --> 01:14:55,757
  and admit to our heartfelt

897
01:14:55,838 --> 01:14:58,140
          attraction.

898
01:14:58,641 --> 01:15:00,875
I'm not sure how you spell "attraction".

899
01:15:03,012 --> 01:15:04,078
        How about...

900
01:15:04,579 --> 01:15:08,049
    "heartfelt desires"?

901
01:15:08,550 --> 01:15:10,949
  Are you sure you want to do this?

902
01:15:11,220 --> 01:15:14,682
    ...heartfelt desires,

903
01:15:14,723 --> 01:15:17,259
            dearest

904
01:15:18,260 --> 01:15:19,962
            Joseph

905
01:15:20,663 --> 01:15:22,997
         [ DOG BARKING ]

906
01:15:22,998 --> 01:15:25,400
 - Look at that.
 Just acovered with gore.

907
01:15:25,701 --> 01:15:27,001
            Dogs didn't do all that.

908
01:15:29,805 --> 01:15:31,372
  Are you drawing breath, son?

909
01:15:31,873 --> 01:15:35,244
    Baldwins, we were sold...

910
01:15:36,045 --> 01:15:36,944
   - What's your name?

911
01:15:37,455 --> 01:15:39,213
            Bosephus...

912
01:15:40,014 --> 01:15:42,217
        Sephus Purcell.

913
01:15:42,818 --> 01:15:44,353
         - Kin to Nimrod Purcell?  

914
01:15:46,354 --> 01:15:47,955
     That's daddy's uncle.

915
01:15:49,224 --> 01:15:51,222
Say some Baldwin agents took ya?

916
01:15:53,295 --> 01:15:55,063
          From behind.

917
01:15:55,364 --> 01:15:58,866
 - None of them Purcells
 ever was too bright.

918
01:16:00,002 --> 01:16:03,071
Grab his ankles missus and mind your dress.

919
01:16:03,072 --> 01:16:05,206
He's ableedin' like a stuck pig.

920
01:16:16,452 --> 01:16:18,820
  I found 'em boys, he's here.

921
01:16:23,892 --> 01:16:25,227
         - It's Reese.

922
01:16:35,204 --> 01:16:36,871
     Got yourself a martyr.

923
01:16:39,308 --> 01:16:41,509
     I tried to stop this.

924
01:16:43,479 --> 01:16:45,447
      See any sign of Sephus?

925
01:16:47,249 --> 01:16:50,118
We'll maybe smell him before we see him.

926
01:16:56,525 --> 01:16:57,952
     They found somebody?

927
01:16:57,993 --> 01:17:00,996
  Just stay right here, honey,
don't want to look at that mess.

928
01:17:01,497 --> 01:17:03,631
But, I got somethin for Mr. Kenehan.

929
01:17:05,300 --> 01:17:07,769
I don't think he's in no mood
to be bothered right now.

930
01:17:08,370 --> 01:17:09,704
      I'll see he gets it.

931
01:17:12,351 --> 01:17:13,575
          Who is it?

932
01:17:13,876 --> 01:17:18,412
 Oh, just some poor miner
 whose troubles is finally over.

933
01:17:19,882 --> 01:17:21,159
    Don't look, honey.

934
01:17:23,318 --> 01:17:27,422
 I talked to Ellix.
He says your phonograph machine

935
01:17:27,423 --> 01:17:30,225
is going to be fixed in a couple days now.

936
01:17:31,026 --> 01:17:33,328
  It's awful nice of you to do, Everett.

937
01:17:33,929 --> 01:17:37,665
Well, we got to take care of
our favorite lady now, don't we?

938
01:17:39,335 --> 01:17:41,406
    - You been so generous...

939
01:17:41,443 --> 01:17:44,032
thinking about me when that Mr. Kenehan

940
01:17:44,073 --> 01:17:46,573
got you all so busy with the union.

941
01:17:48,644 --> 01:17:50,948
That Mr. Kenehan is what I come
  to talk to you about, Bridey.

942
01:17:53,982 --> 01:17:58,252
 I got a suspicion he
might not be what he says he is.

943
01:17:59,153 --> 01:18:00,521
    What do you mean?

944
01:18:05,861 --> 01:18:07,328
            Bridey,

945
01:18:07,729 --> 01:18:10,731
did you send Kenehan some sort of letter?

946
01:18:36,992 --> 01:18:38,126
    What do you want?

947
01:18:39,995 --> 01:18:41,763
              No.

948
01:18:42,064 --> 01:18:44,032
          He wouldn't.

949
01:18:44,433 --> 01:18:47,568
There's a whole crowd of fellas
  standing around him,

950
01:18:47,769 --> 01:18:50,054
 I seen Kenehan laughing and waving that letter.

951
01:18:50,105 --> 01:18:52,076
             So, I

952
01:18:52,107 --> 01:18:54,475
  come over to see what was so funny.

953
01:18:55,911 --> 01:18:58,313
    A lot of fellers?

954
01:19:01,783 --> 01:19:04,318
You mind if i have another drink, honey?

955
01:19:06,688 --> 01:19:08,789
It ain't pretty what I gotta say.

956
01:19:21,236 --> 01:19:23,401
  He said some things, Bridey...

957
01:19:23,438 --> 01:19:28,443
  "She been following me around
     ever since I got here.

958
01:19:28,644 --> 01:19:32,513
"Trailing after me
like a dog in heat.

959
01:19:32,614 --> 01:19:35,443
 "Sniffing around my legs
 like a brood bitch.

960
01:19:35,484 --> 01:19:38,809
  "She don't wear no drawers",
  he says, "so she can be ready for

961
01:19:38,840 --> 01:19:40,815
whatever stumbles down the pathway."

962
01:19:40,856 --> 01:19:42,590
          He didn't!

963
01:19:47,763 --> 01:19:49,564
        He didn't!

964
01:19:51,967 --> 01:19:55,136
He said you done it
with one of the coloreds.

965
01:19:56,672 --> 01:19:58,473
         Lying bastard!

966
01:19:58,674 --> 01:19:59,807
            Bridey,

967
01:19:59,976 --> 01:20:02,543
 I think it might be worse than that.

968
01:20:03,344 --> 01:20:05,907
I think he might be a spy

969
01:20:05,948 --> 01:20:08,075
  in with the coal operators.

970
01:20:08,316 --> 01:20:12,186
  Well, he's got the fellas so
turned around with all his talk...

971
01:20:14,156 --> 01:20:16,380
I need for you to help me, Bridey,

972
01:20:16,401 --> 01:20:19,894
 and sometimes you gotta tell
 a little bit of a lie

973
01:20:19,995 --> 01:20:23,264
 just to get the truth across.

974
01:20:24,566 --> 01:20:26,531
    We fight them with guns

975
01:20:26,568 --> 01:20:28,169
            we lose.

976
01:20:29,671 --> 01:20:31,505
  That's the whole damn story.

977
01:20:33,075 --> 01:20:35,870
 I'm not going to bullshit
you fellas and tell you there won't

978
01:20:35,911 --> 01:20:38,379
  ever come a time when    
  the people that own this state     

979
01:20:38,410 --> 01:20:40,284
send the word down to
have us all murdered.

980
01:20:40,745 --> 01:20:43,150
 But, if we don't stand together now

981
01:20:43,151 --> 01:20:47,088
as workers, we got no hope at all.

982
01:21:02,371 --> 01:21:03,237
          Help me up.

983
01:21:04,139 --> 01:21:05,306
     You going somewhere?

984
01:21:05,707 --> 01:21:09,910
This is miner's business
and you ain't no miner.

985
01:21:11,847 --> 01:21:13,414
    You two come along.

986
01:21:26,128 --> 01:21:27,527
            So, ah...

