and you got all these little ones,

1227
01:43:15,255 --> 01:43:16,602
            well...

1228
01:43:18,405 --> 01:43:21,508
You know what to do with this?

1229
01:43:22,009 --> 01:43:24,010
      Hillard brung it in.

1230
01:43:25,946 --> 01:43:26,912
          It's for you.

1231
01:43:28,549 --> 01:43:32,219
I ain't gonna watch no babies go hungry,
now here you go on.

1232
01:43:33,920 --> 01:43:36,455
    Here is some navy beans

1233
01:43:37,356 --> 01:43:42,538
and these here is ramps.
Now you can cook with these.

1234
01:43:42,596 --> 01:43:45,331
 They put a taste in your stew.

1235
01:43:51,205 --> 01:43:52,339
            Anyhow...

1236
01:44:10,391 --> 01:44:12,201
        Well, I...

1237
01:44:12,437 --> 01:44:15,629
figure we's all in this together.

1238
01:44:19,867 --> 01:44:22,268
You sure got some pretty babies.

1239
01:44:26,740 --> 01:44:28,855
 Who's your favorite pitcher?
          - Hod Eller.

1240
01:44:28,886 --> 01:44:31,046
    He's from Logan county.

1241
01:44:33,147 --> 01:44:35,315
 - You get to play ball much?

1242
01:44:35,916 --> 01:44:37,650
When the mines were open.

1243
01:44:43,023 --> 01:44:44,258
             Joe...

1244
01:44:45,059 --> 01:44:46,392
             Yeah?

1245
01:44:46,693 --> 01:44:48,528
    You ever kill anybody?

1246
01:44:51,665 --> 01:44:53,533
     What brought that up?

1247
01:44:54,434 --> 01:44:56,303
          Bet Sid has.

1248
01:44:56,754 --> 01:44:58,738
        He were in the war.

1249
01:45:01,809 --> 01:45:05,210
 All I saw was workers killin' workers

1250
01:45:05,979 --> 01:45:07,761
 and there wasn't any point in it.

1251
01:45:07,795 --> 01:45:10,617
 They thrown you in jail
cause you wouldn't go?

1252
01:45:10,918 --> 01:45:14,514
  Them two years kept me from
killin' some poor stiff that got

1253
01:45:14,555 --> 01:45:18,257
 pushed out on a battlefield
 by rich folks and politicians,

1254
01:45:19,760 --> 01:45:21,694
    and they were worth it.

1255
01:45:29,269 --> 01:45:31,071
    It's gettin' dark, Danny.

1256
01:45:33,874 --> 01:45:36,576
  You better go get that coal.

1257
01:46:01,335 --> 01:46:05,104
 You see there,
right there by the railroad trestle?

1258
01:46:06,140 --> 01:46:08,207
 That's where Cap Hatfield
 and his boy Joe Glenn

1259
01:46:08,241 --> 01:46:09,742
             killed three men.

1260
01:46:10,591 --> 01:46:12,166
    Boy wasn't but 13.

1261
01:46:12,199 --> 01:46:14,214
    Used a Winchester.

1262
01:46:17,584 --> 01:46:19,919
You think it hurts much, a bullet?

1263
01:46:21,655 --> 01:46:24,856
Beats dying in a damn coal mine.

1264
01:46:27,461 --> 01:46:30,463
 Boy wasn't but 13 year old, Joe Glenn.

1265
01:46:50,417 --> 01:46:52,218
    Must be in there.

1266
01:46:52,719 --> 01:46:54,654
He always sleeps with the lights on.

1267
01:46:54,855 --> 01:46:57,223
  Just gotta be quiet is all.

1268
01:47:15,242 --> 01:47:18,477
        [ GUNSHOT ]
- Let's get the little bastards.

1269
01:47:21,615 --> 01:47:23,382
        - Over here.

1270
01:47:25,052 --> 01:47:26,886
    - Grab him, cut him off.

1271
01:47:33,927 --> 01:47:36,533
- Well, well what we got here?

1272
01:47:37,568 --> 01:47:40,099
 Smarts a little don't it boy?

1273
01:47:40,300 --> 01:47:41,969
        Hillard, right?

1274
01:47:42,670 --> 01:47:46,007
 Now, how about you
 give us the names of

1275
01:47:46,108 --> 01:47:48,475
 your ring leaders up in Logan?

1276
01:47:48,976 --> 01:47:53,179
Give us 5 names boy, that's all,
 5 names and we'll let you go.

1277
01:47:53,480 --> 01:47:55,615
     That's fair isn't it?
            - Never.

1278
01:47:56,016 --> 01:47:57,351
            Griggsy...

1279
01:48:01,088 --> 01:48:03,122
        Talk to us boy.
         [ PUNCHES HIM ]

1280
01:48:04,591 --> 01:48:07,163
          Talk to us!

1281
01:48:07,197 --> 01:48:10,229
    I'll rot in hell first.
      - Have it your way.

1282
01:48:11,331 --> 01:48:13,966
          Mr. Lively.

1283
01:48:34,087 --> 01:48:37,594
Boy, I sentence you to death
for the crime of

1284
01:48:37,635 --> 01:48:39,258
       stealing Company property

1285
01:48:39,459 --> 01:48:42,229
  and being a dirty bolshevist union man.

1286
01:48:43,230 --> 01:48:45,265
  You got 10 seconds to talk.

1287
01:49:21,267 --> 01:49:22,401
                       - Talk.  

1288
01:49:27,974 --> 01:49:31,144
 - Whoo, what a smell,              
 Boy dirtied his diapers.               

1289
01:49:31,545 --> 01:49:33,180
- We want names, son.  

1290
01:49:34,081 --> 01:49:35,061
            I can't,

1291
01:49:35,192 --> 01:49:37,484
     I sworn on a bible.

1292
01:49:38,085 --> 01:49:41,089
- Then we're going to have
to get down to it son.

1292
01:49:41,585 --> 01:49:42,989
- Use the razor. 

1293
01:49:43,590 --> 01:49:44,625
- Hold him boys. 

1294
01:49:49,930 --> 01:49:51,952
    Just a little nick, boy.

1295
01:49:58,872 --> 01:50:01,240
- Get it off your chest, son.

1296
01:50:03,877 --> 01:50:11,384
  Plyant Mount, Bill Mahan,
  Asa Radnor, J.T. Keadle...

1297
01:50:13,019 --> 01:50:16,156
    5, give us 5, boy.

1298
01:50:16,957 --> 01:50:18,057
    And Harley Shilton.

1299
01:50:18,658 --> 01:50:20,259
- Kill him.
    NO!

1300
01:50:42,215 --> 01:50:44,451
So where do them fellas he named live?

1301
01:50:44,952 --> 01:50:46,119
       Clay Hill.

1302
01:50:46,520 --> 01:50:48,387
         Where's that?

1303
01:50:48,888 --> 01:50:50,991
        It's a cemetery.

1304
01:50:51,992 --> 01:50:54,094
  Them are all fellas that was

1305
01:50:54,135 --> 01:50:56,395
killed in a gas fire 5-6 years ago.

1306
01:51:08,408 --> 01:51:11,814
Nothin' like a young boy dyin'

1307
01:51:11,845 --> 01:51:14,013
    to stir things up.

1308
01:51:30,397 --> 01:51:35,501
    [ CRYING IN THE DISTANCE ]

1309
01:52:02,929 --> 01:52:05,731
Baldwin's coming into town tomorrow, Kenehan.

1310
01:52:37,764 --> 01:52:40,503
You fellas have any idea
what's waiting for us?

1311
01:52:41,534 --> 01:52:43,335
You mean they didn't tell you?

1312
01:52:43,370 --> 01:52:45,106
 No. I just seen a line in the papers of...

1313
01:52:45,137 --> 01:52:48,437
...'Opportunity for red-blooded American men...        

1314
01:52:48,475 --> 01:52:50,402
 'Immediate openings, high pay            

1315
01:52:50,443 --> 01:52:55,361
 'travel, chance for advancement.       
 Apply Baldwin Felts and            

1316
01:52:55,392 --> 01:52:56,699
 'write your own ticket.'              

1317
01:52:56,750 --> 01:52:59,886
When the natives get restless someplace
they put that out.

1317
01:53:00,750 --> 01:53:03,486
Hook some more cannon fodder.

1318
01:53:04,891 --> 01:53:07,363
 Ever hear of the
 Hatfields and McCoys, son?

1319
01:53:07,394 --> 01:53:08,955
     Yeah, of course I have.

1320
01:53:09,196 --> 01:53:11,601
 This Matewan is their stomping grounds.

1321
01:53:11,631 --> 01:53:15,534
  They'll put a bullet in your brain
as soon as they look at ya.

1322
01:53:20,073 --> 01:53:23,256
 Sid, we have authorization
 to put these miners

1323
01:53:23,287 --> 01:53:25,444
off Company property here in town.

1324
01:53:25,545 --> 01:53:27,129
     Not from me you don't.

1325
01:53:27,280 --> 01:53:29,285
  And we also got
a warrant for your arrest,

1326
01:53:29,316 --> 01:53:31,016
    you give us any trouble.

1327
01:53:36,389 --> 01:53:39,325
 This ain't worth shit and you know it.

1328
01:53:40,927 --> 01:53:43,829
 One way or another we're going
  to carry out these evictions,

1329
01:53:43,860 --> 01:53:44,940
    tomorrow morning.

1330
01:53:46,733 --> 01:53:48,701
        Gentleman.

1331
01:54:04,184 --> 01:54:06,519
      They come to kill me.

1332
01:54:18,632 --> 01:54:22,335
     Hillard was my friend.

1333
01:54:22,836 --> 01:54:26,129
 When I first come down to the
mines it was Hillard who'd

1334
01:54:26,159 --> 01:54:27,953
       show me what to do.

1335
01:54:27,994 --> 01:54:31,954
He was a good coal miner,
a good union man.

1336
01:54:32,245 --> 01:54:35,014
 And he always took care of his mama.

1337
01:54:37,117 --> 01:54:40,853
I don't know how they could have
    done him like they did.

1338
01:54:43,189 --> 01:54:46,558
  All he wanted to do was
  live decent, that's all.

1339
01:54:48,561 --> 01:54:51,731
  Sometimes people say how God
willed it, how everything is

1340
01:54:51,782 --> 01:54:53,532
            His plan.

1341
01:54:55,970 --> 01:55:01,069
Well... I don't think He planned
on Hillard a'laying here amongst

1342
01:55:01,107 --> 01:55:04,036
  all these Elkinses.
Not this young in his life.

1343
01:55:04,077 --> 01:55:07,414
I think all God plans is
we get born and we

1344
01:55:07,465 --> 01:55:09,348
  got to take it from there.

1345
01:55:11,117 --> 01:55:13,285
 So you rest in peace, Hillard.

1346
01:55:14,288 --> 01:55:17,790
You rest easy cause we're going
to take up where you left off.

1347
01:55:22,595 --> 01:55:23,629
             Amen.

1348
01:55:31,205 --> 01:55:34,039
 You gonna tell us to
turn the other cheek, still?

1349
01:55:36,509 --> 01:55:38,842
Shootin' is what they want now.

1350
01:55:39,878 --> 01:55:42,280
Maybe it's what we want, too.

1351
01:55:45,185 --> 01:55:47,786
You expect too much of people, Joe.

1352
01:55:49,889 --> 01:55:53,258
 Your still after that one big union,
but most of us,

1353
01:55:53,889 --> 01:55:56,462
 we can't see past this hollar.

1354
01:55:57,263 --> 01:56:06,812
      ♫ [ SINGING GOSPEL ] ♫

1355
01:56:51,116 --> 01:56:53,052
I need to talk to the men.

1356
01:56:55,288 --> 01:56:57,523
        Wouldn't be decent now.

1357
01:57:01,427 --> 01:57:04,329
I'll call a meeting in the morning,

1358
01:57:04,930 --> 01:57:06,859
          first thing.

1359
01:57:12,472 --> 01:57:18,927
 ♫ [ GOSPEL SINGING CONTINUES ] ♫

1360
01:57:54,614 --> 01:57:57,217
Pass the word to stay out from town tomorrow.

1361
01:57:58,918 --> 01:58:01,020
 Something up?

1362
01:58:03,823 --> 01:58:07,493
Got a feelin'.
You know how white folks is

1363
01:58:07,524 --> 01:58:10,861
 when they gets all excited.

1364
01:59:09,322 --> 01:59:11,990
Nothin's gonna bring Hillard back you know.

1365
01:59:14,327 --> 01:59:16,529
    Danny, I came here to help.

1366
01:59:17,830 --> 01:59:18,998
         Sure you did.

1367
01:59:20,799 --> 01:59:23,434
 First people come here
to help us with some money.

1368
01:59:25,007 --> 01:59:27,303
  Next we know we got no land.

1369
01:59:27,440 --> 01:59:29,979
 Then they say they're going
 to help us with a job and

1370
01:59:30,010 --> 01:59:31,777
 a place to live

1371
01:59:31,848 --> 01:59:34,313
 and they stick us in some
       damn coal camp 

1372
01:59:34,354 --> 01:59:37,517
and let us dig out their mines.

1373
01:59:38,018 --> 01:59:42,687
  Now you come here to help us
     bring in the 'new day'.

1374
01:59:43,556 --> 01:59:46,959
Well, Hillard ain't gonna see no new day.

1375
01:59:47,760 --> 01:59:50,362
We had about as much help as we can stand.

1376
01:59:51,497 --> 01:59:53,465
We gotta take care of ourselves.

1377
01:59:56,002 --> 01:59:58,470
  We got to take care of each other.

1378
02:00:49,222 --> 02:00:53,068
♫ [ HARMONICA PLAYING BLUES ] ♫

1379
02:01:37,670 --> 02:01:41,251
 Joe!. Joe! The men go to town.

1380
02:01:53,252 --> 02:01:54,787
            See 'em?

1381
02:01:57,123 --> 02:01:59,558
No need for you to be in on this.

1382
02:02:00,126 --> 02:02:04,696
  It's my town too, they're my people.

1383
02:03:13,533 --> 02:03:16,363
 Y'all have no right to come to
 this here town with all these people

1384
02:03:16,397 --> 02:03:18,517
and drawing guns and terrorizing them.

1385
02:03:18,558 --> 02:03:20,542
The writs you have are
not valid for this town.

1386
02:03:20,577 --> 02:03:23,608
     If you can't get one..
            - NO!!!!!

1387
02:03:23,709 --> 02:03:24,777
             Oh...

1388
02:05:08,381 --> 02:05:10,448
     Jesus, don't shoot me.

1389
02:06:25,024 --> 02:06:27,258
      I just wanted to talk.

1390
02:06:30,730 --> 02:06:32,831
      I just wanted to talk.

1391
02:06:37,903 --> 02:06:39,418
          [ GUN FIRING ]

1392
02:06:40,449 --> 02:06:42,341
     I can't feel my legs.

1393
02:07:23,249 --> 02:07:26,887
        [ SOFTLY SOBBING ]

1394
02:07:55,014 --> 02:07:58,517
<i>There was a trial but there
  wasn't nobody going to pass</i>

1395
02:07:58,568 --> 02:08:02,257
<i>guilty on Sid Hatfield in Mingo county</i>.

1396
02:08:02,328 --> 02:08:05,557
<i>Sid got married to mayor Testerman's widow</i>

1397
02:08:05,588 --> 02:08:07,472
<i>and then the Baldwins
they caught him unarmed</i>

1398
02:08:07,503 --> 02:08:10,895
<i>walking up the steps of the
  McDowell county court house</i>.

1399
02:08:10,956 --> 02:08:13,268
<i>They shot 15 bullets into him</i>,

1400
02:08:13,299 --> 02:08:18,082
<i>right in broad daylight and
C.E. Lively stepped in and put one</i>

1401
02:08:18,115 --> 02:08:19,931
<i>right through his skull</i>.

1402
02:08:19,972 --> 02:08:22,474
<i>Wasn't even a trial on that one</i>.

1403
02:08:22,975 --> 02:08:26,876
<i>That was the start of the
great Coalfield War and us miners</i>

1404
02:08:26,912 --> 02:08:29,160
<i>took the worst of it,
like Joe said we would</i>.

1405
02:08:29,194 --> 02:08:33,304
  <i>'It's just one big union
the whole world over'</i>,

1406
02:08:33,339 --> 02:08:34,853
<i>as Joe Kenehan used to say</i>.

1407
02:08:34,887 --> 02:08:37,901
<i>And from the day of the Matewan massacre
that's what I preached</i>.

1408
02:08:37,935 --> 02:08:40,358
<i>That was my religion</i>.

1409
02:08:41,859 --> 02:08:45,357
<i>We buried Joe Kenehan with our own</i>.

1410
02:08:45,698 --> 02:08:48,100
<i>My mama she thought
he wouldn't never stay</i>,

1411
02:08:48,501 --> 02:08:50,769
<i>but now he's with us for always</i>,

1412
02:08:51,803 --> 02:08:54,739
<i>laying up here in these
  West Virginia hills</i>.

1413
02:09:03,082 --> 02:09:11,163
